'''Laura Slessinger'''

Talk radio host Laura Slessinger's favorite strategy with a caller is to apply an infinite regression of "So what?"'s to the feared consequences that would result from the caller taking her advice.  The question "So what?" seems to strike directly at the dominant function, leaving it dazed and speechless, perhaps forcing a person to reverse attitudes.
